{
  "local_port": 48554,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I have a problem with coupon set up. I have created a coupon in WooCommerce and I want it to be applied to the product on sale. I have also removed the check from the exclude sale item. But still it's not applying that coupon to products which are on sale. How can I fix it?",
  "response": "If you\u2019ve created a coupon in WooCommerce and removed the \"Exclude sale items\" option but it\u2019s still not applying to products on sale, there are a few things you can check and troubleshoot to resolve the issue:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Verify Coupon Settings**\n   - **Coupon Type**: Ensure the coupon type (e.g., percentage discount, fixed cart discount, etc.) is compatible with the sale price.\n   - **Exclude Sale Items**: Double-check that the \"Exclude sale items\" box is unchecked in the coupon settings.\n   - **Product/Category Restrictions**: Make sure the coupon is not restricted to specific products or categories that exclude the sale items.\n   - **Usage Limits**: Ensure the coupon hasn\u2019t reached its usage limit.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Check Product Sale Price**\n   - Verify that the product is actually on sale. Go to the product\u2019s edit page and ensure the \"Sale Price\" field is filled in.\n   - Check if the sale price is active (the \"Sale price\" field should have a value, and the \"Schedule\" should be set correctly if applicable).\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Coupon Applicability**\n   - **Cart Conditions**: Ensure the coupon meets the cart conditions (e.g., minimum/maximum spend, quantity, etc.).\n   - **Product-Specific Coupons**: If the coupon is restricted to specific products or categories, ensure the sale item is included in the allowed products/categories.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Clear Cache**\n   - If you\u2019re using a caching plugin or server-side caching, clear the cache to ensure changes are reflected.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Check for Plugin or Theme Conflicts**\n   - Disable all plugins except WooCommerce and test the coupon again. If it works, re-enable plugins one by one to identify the conflicting plugin.\n   - Switch to a default WordPress theme (e.g., Twenty Twenty-Three) to rule out a theme-related issue.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Check JavaScript Errors**\n   - Open the browser\u2019s developer tools (F12) and look for JavaScript errors on the cart/checkout page that might prevent the coupon from being applied.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Test with a Default Coupon**\n   - Create a new, simple coupon with minimal restrictions (e.g., no product or category restrictions) and test if it applies to the sale item. This will help determine if the issue is specific to the original coupon or a broader problem.\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Debugging Options**\n   - Enable WooCommerce debugging by adding the following to your `wp-config.php` file:\n     ```php\n     define('WP_DEBUG', true);\n     define('WP_DEBUG_LOG', true);\n     define('WP_DEBUG_DISPLAY', false);\n     ```\n   - Check the WooCommerce logs (`WooCommerce > Status > Logs`) for any errors related to coupons.\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Ensure No Overlapping Discounts**\n   - If you have other coupons or discounts active, ensure they\u2019re not conflicting with the coupon you\u2019re testing.\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Update WooCommerce**\n   - Ensure you\u2019re using the latest version of WooCommerce, as bugs related to coupons may have been fixed in newer versions.\n\n---\n\nIf none of the above steps resolve the issue, consider reaching out to WooCommerce support or your theme/plugin developer for further assistance. Let me know if you need help with any specific step!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
